I lost my grandpa a year ago. He raised me, and I called him dad. Itâ€™s been so very hard, and there is never anything anyone can say to make it hurt less.....but a warm hug and making sure we surround ourselves with people who love us is great therapy for the heart. Of course, sometimes we want to grieve alone, and thatâ€™s ok, too. At times, I cry in the shower when Iâ€™ve had a rough day. For a while, I didnâ€™t cry for months; but all of a sudden, on the anniversary of his passing, I broke down and cried in the shower two days in a row. Sometimes, you think you are doing so good living with the sad reality of their absence, but the next second it could hurt so bad all over again. Itâ€™s so weird....to grieve. It truly never ends until, well....the end. I know you probably wonâ€™t read this....but I guess this is me grieving right now on this video, because your video truly saddened me for the both of us.
